p: Against the normalized time (days / median), the stage-specific frequency distribution of C. krombeini was also described by the Weibull model: egg (F 1,39 = 1563.9, P < 0.01, r 2 = 0.976), larva (F 1,40 = 1847.5, P < 0.01, r 2 = 0.979), nymph (F 1,50 = 992.0, P < 0.01, r 2 = 0.953), and egg to adult (F 1,54 = 935.2, P < 0.01, r 2 = 0.946) ( Table 2, Fig 2).
